README

Creating a new ROS Service

roscreate-pkg package_name depend1 depend2 .. 

If current dir is not in ROS path, must change ROS_PACKAGE_PATH environment variable to include it
--> people online recommend not modifying /opt/ros/*
http://www.ros.org/wiki/ROS/EnvironmentVariables

Add this line to your ~/.bashrc directly under the call to /opt/ros/distro/setup.bash:
export ROS_PACKAGE_PATH=~/ros_workspace:${ROS_PACKAGE_PATH}
FROM http://answers.ros.org/question/30586/how-to-change-ros_package_path/

.bashrc changes will persist in next command line instance

Make your srv directory

Create serviceType.srv with
Request message type(s)
---
Repsonse message type(s)

http://www.ros.org/wiki/srv
http://www.ros.org/wiki/ROS/Tutorials/CreatingMsgAndSrv#Creating_a_srv

Uncomment # rosbuild_gensrv() from CMakeList.txt

rosmake the package again


